======================================================================
14. ROLLBACK / FLASHBACK DECISION MATRIX
======================================================================

CASE A - FAILURE BEFORE DATAPATCH STARTS
ACTION:
- keep DG isolated
- stop any started primary
- modify Oracle Home back to previous home
- enable/start primary from old home
- no flashback required
- standbys remain down / unchanged until command decision

CASE B - FAILURE AFTER DATAPATCH ON PRIMARY BUT BEFORE STANDBY HOME SWITCH
ACTION:
- keep GDS disabled
- keep DG isolated
- stop primary
- startup mount primary
- flashback primary to GRP
- open resetlogs only by command decision
- revert primary Oracle Home to old home if required
- do not bring standbys up casually
- DG recovery plan must be coordinated by DG lead before resuming transport

PRIMARY FLASHBACK COMMANDS:
sqlplus / as sysdba <<EOF
shutdown immediate;
startup mount;
flashback database to restore point '<GRP_NAME>';
alter database open resetlogs;
EOF

CASE C - FAILURE AFTER STANDBY HOME SWITCH BUT BEFORE DG IS HEALTHY
ACTION:
- keep GDS disabled
- do not enable services
- stop and assess by command decision
- flashback / DG re-establishment may be required
- treat this as DG recovery event, not simple rollback

CASE D - FAILURE AFTER GDS IS RESTORED
ACTION:
- stop / disable affected GDS pool immediately
- contain traffic first
- then decide whether to repair forward or execute DG / flashback recovery

IMPORTANT:
- GRP is a fail-check anchor, not a promise that rollback is trivial
- once resetlogs / DG state changes are involved, DG lead must own the decision
- do not improvise flashback + standby reopen steps

